Strange  that I got two very different failures, both unrelated to my changes. I have not seen either of these issues before.  
1) seabase/031 - an objectID did not get filtered in test output.
2) jdbc test cleanup failed to drop a table.
      BatchTest>JdbcCommon.doBaseTestCleanup:149->JdbcCommon.dropTestObjects:218 Failed to drop object: table BATCH_TEST_TABLE

All the test jobs have passed, just not all on the same run.

Hi Steve - jdbc failure seems to be related to TRAFODION-2695 -  saw similar error in 
https://jenkins.esgyn.com/job/jdbc_test-cdh/2464/console. Will check with @selvaganesang  if they are related and if any testware modification is needed.

On second look, there seems to be lot of unneeded code/confusion in the surround code. The error message that is supposed to contain the original data is not consistently done in all the error conditions. This change seems to take care a certain error message paths alone. 

So, I will let the author to decide if the code change needs to go in or out.  I am ok with either of the conclusions.
